HEADWORD: Corkage
<hw>Cork"age</hw> <pr>(-⟦asl⟧j)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The charge made
by innkeepers for drawing the cork and taking care of bottles of wine
bought elsewhere by a guest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corked</ent>⟦br⟧
